</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/12/02 9:53:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22779.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ok</span><hr size=1> There are quite a few mobs that are not fooled by sneak at all. Luckily you can tell which ones by the fact that they will con scowling to you while you are sneaked behind them.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usaevanjnoir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saevan JNoir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/12/02 10:27:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22779.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ok</span><hr size=1> Sorry, I should have been clearer about the spiders in DL/FV. They don't all see through hide, just enough of them to be annoying.<br>
<br>
As for conning KOS while sneaking behind a mob, have you ever been attacked? AFAIK this is just a bad con message (in EQ ... say it ain't so!!?).   <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=10371>Saevan J’Noir - Teir'Dal Blackguard</a><br>Siege</br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzepf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>zepf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/12/02 11:08:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22779.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ok</span><hr size=1> FV spideys dont see thru H/S at all.  i am ALWAYS goin in n' out of FV and loio and not ONCE hasa spidey seen me while in H/S... maybe im just lucky, but theyve never seen thru my H/S ever. <p>"You seem a decent fellow...I hate to die."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=elegance>Elegance</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/12/02 11:23:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22779.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ok</span><hr size=1> &quot;Bats in Lguk dont see hide, impossible to get the DE mask at level 10 if they did.&quot;<br>
<br>
no they really do see through hide, you get your mask by hugging the wall which puts you just out of agro range.  I have seen itu'ed folks run through that room by hugging the wall so its not even a sneak issue.  if you dont believe me go sneak and hide your way up to one of the lguk bats and come back and let us know if they tried to eat you or not. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uinkiewiz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Inkiewiz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/12/02 12:28:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22779.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.strike9.com/eq/file.aspx/path=/inkiewiz/fullsize/iriasmall3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ok</span><hr size=1> &lt;&lt;FV spideys dont see thru H/S at all.&gt;&gt;<br>
<br>
They can see through hide if they've cast see invis on themselves (or another). I always conned them, and once found one that was scowling.  Waited for him to wander off.<br>
<br>
I gather this is true of most any caster mob, or mobs that are &quot;grouped&quot; with caster mobs.  So, basically, always con. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uandrewbb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AndrewBB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/12/02 12:46:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22779.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ok</span><hr size=1> Interesting observation about chodakai sniffers in Chardok... they don't so much see invis as they *smell* you. <br>
<br>
You can be invis within aggro range and they won't attack, but step close enough and they'll tag you.<br>
<br>
No idea if sneak works on them... if so, I guess you're 'downwind' of them...<br>
<br>
Bats in LGuk/SolB have sonar, so they're not fooled by hide or invisibility. <br>
<br>
Just doing my little bit to help add to the suspension of disbelief... and it's nice to know that for at least some of these mobs, it makes _sense_ that they see us. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umylene.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mylene</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.columbus.rr.com/miri311/KR3_04.GIF" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/12/02 1:01:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22779.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.columbus.rr.com/miri311/JEANFACE2.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ok</span><hr size=1> My understanding of mobs that can see through normal invis yet cannot see rogue hide/sneak is that these mobs were given undead seeing abilities, regardless of how the mob is coded as a type overall. An example would be Kobalds in Sol B.<br>
<br>
The Kobalds are defenitly not undead, yet they see like undead mobs. Hence, only hiding rogues are invisible to them. I'd imagine the Drolvargs in DL are coded in a similar fashion.<br>
<br>
-Mylene <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulannellavelglarn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lannella Velglarn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.boomspeed.com/lannella/leaf.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/12/02 2:23:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22779.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www3.sympatico.ca/housecalls/nextlevel.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ok</span><hr size=1> Drachnids are a 'ranger' mob and may have buffed themselves/each other with SeeInvis.  I've only been spotted by one once ever so it's not common.<br>
<br>
KC dogs sometimes do - that seems to be more innate than drachnids.<br>
(I've not spent enough time in Chardok to have much opinion there)<br>
<br>
<br>
