Current spot: Dreadlands (my favorite zone thus far) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usakharra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sakharra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/12/02 5:31:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22779.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EMP CRUSH</span><hr size=1> Specs near the Fear portal do see hide if in front arc but are not sensative enough to see sneak if you are behind them...<br>
<br>
For some reason, thats one train I never remember to call if I'm running late for a Fear raid.  (sorry about the specs Cindy campers).  <br>
<br>
Sakharra<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ularcenmistwalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Larcen Mistwalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/12/02 5:35:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22779.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ok</span><hr size=1> The bats and the Greater Ice Bones in Lower Guk both see through hide.  However, the aggro range on both is extremely small so if you hug the walls they won't aggro.   Hide is basically like a slightly superior invisibility, but a slightly inferior IVU ( Greater Ice Bones in LG don't see through IVU ) combined.  Combine that with sneak and you can get into a lot of places that others can't.   <p><img src="http://www.twilite.org/~chrome/images/sigs/larcensig.jpg" border="0">
